---
import Section from './Section.astro';
---

<Section background="muted">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <!-- Icon -->
    <div class="flex justify-center mb-8 reveal">
      <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-2xl bg-secondary/10 flex items-center justify-center">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-secondary" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v3.75m-9.303 3.376c-.866 1.5.217 3.374 1.948 3.374h14.71c1.73 0 2.813-1.874 1.948-3.374L13.949 3.378c-.866-1.5-3.032-1.5-3.898 0L2.697 16.126zM12 15.75h.007v.008H12v-.008z" />
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center">
      <h2 class="font-heading font-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-6 reveal">
        Checking your website across screen sizes is a pain
      </h2>
      <p class="text-foreground/60 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6 reveal reveal-delay-1">
        You push a change and want to see how it looks. But your preview is buried in a dashboard somewhere — Cloudflare, GitHub, Vercel, Netlify — and even when you find the link, you can only see it at whatever screen size you're on.
      </p>
      <p class="text-foreground/60 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-8 reveal reveal-delay-2">
        Want to check the desktop layout from your phone? You're stuck waiting until you're back at your desk.
      </p>

      <!-- Transition line -->
      <div class="reveal reveal-delay-3 flex items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <div class="h-px w-12 bg-primary/30"></div>
        <p class="text-primary dark:text-indigo-300 font-heading font-semibold text-lg">
          There's a better way
        </p>
        <div class="h-px w-12 bg-primary/30"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Section>
